<task id="032" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>P2-CLOSEOUT-01 Wire ChatDocumentEndpoints.UploadDocumentAsync into R5 session-files pipeline</title>
    <status>✅</status>
    <status-note>Closeout task added 2026-06-04 after SC-18 walkthrough on Spaarke Dev surfaced Sev-1 integration gap: R5 backend pieces all deployed but upload endpoint never calls IndexSessionFileAsync nor populates ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]. See notes/summarize-vertical-remediation-plan.md §3.1 for full root-cause analysis. Completed 2026-06-04 — see notes/task-032-evidence.md.</status-note>
    <estimated-effort>1.5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~1.5 hours</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration (CLOSEOUT)</phase>
    <wave>P2-G9-CLOSEOUT (parallel-safe with 033; both must complete + deploy before 034)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>011 (Summarize playbook deployed), 003 (RagIndexingPipeline.IndexSessionFileAsync), 004 (ChatSession.UploadedFiles model), 012 (SessionSummarizeOrchestrator consumer)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff-api, chat, session-files, integration, closeout, sev-1-fix</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the existing R3-era chat-document upload endpoint into R5's session-files
    pipeline so that uploaded files become visible to SessionSummarizeOrchestrator
    and the chat agent. This is the missing integration that broke end-to-end
    Summarize on Spaarke Dev (2026-06-04 walkthrough).

    R5 backend pieces ALREADY deployed: IndexSessionFileAsync (task 003),
    SessionSummarizeOrchestrator (task 012), InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool (task
    015), MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint (task 014), ChatSession.UploadedFiles model
    field + ChatSessionFile record (task 004). The deployed playbook
    `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` (task 011, action SUM-CHAT@v1) is ready.
    Nothing actually invokes them from user flows because the upload endpoint
    only writes to Redis (R3 legacy path).

    Modify `ChatDocumentEndpoints.UploadDocumentAsync` (file
    src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs, lines 124-407)
    so that after the existing Redis writes (step 10, ~line 386) AND before the
    202 response (~line 388), it ALSO:

    1. Constructs a `ParsedDocument` from the existing `TextExtractionResult` +
       `originalBinary` already in scope.
    2. Calls `IRagIndexingPipeline.IndexSessionFileAsync(parsedDocument,
       documentId, tenantId, sessionId, speFileId, fileName, ct)` — pass
       documentId as both documentId and speFileId (the latter is a "best
       effort" link for future SPE persistence; for session-uploads we use the
       chat-document GUID as both). Capture the returned chunk IDs.
    3. Constructs a `new ChatSessionFile(documentId, filename, contentType,
       file.Length, searchDocumentIdsCsv, DateTimeOffset.UtcNow)` where
       searchDocumentIdsCsv = `string.Join(",", returnedChunkIds)`.
    4. Defense-in-depth cap check: if `session.UploadedFiles?.Count >=
       ChatSession.MaxUploadedFiles (=20)`, return 400 ProblemDetails with
       errorCode `"summarize.too-many-files"` per NFR-02. (Upstream frontend
       enforces too, but defense in depth at the endpoint boundary mirrors
       SummarizeSessionEndpoint's pattern.)
    5. Builds an updated session record: `session with { UploadedFiles =
       (session.UploadedFiles ?? Array.Empty&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;()).Append(newFile).ToList() }`.
    6. Persists via `sessionManager.UpdateSessionCacheAsync(updatedSession,
       httpContext.RequestAborted)` — this method already exists at line 267
       (internal virtual; refreshes Redis hot cache + fires Cosmos
       write-through per D-06).

    Add `IRagIndexingPipeline` to the endpoint handler's DI parameters
    (alongside existing IDistributedCache, ITextExtractor, ChatSessionManager,
    ILoggerFactory). Verify `AnalysisServicesModule` registers
    `IRagIndexingPipeline` — it does (per task 003 evidence note; bound inside
    the compound AI gate via `AddRagServices`). The upload endpoint already
    requires the compound AI gate (text extraction depends on DocumentIntelligence
    via TextExtractorService); adding IRagIndexingPipeline as a hard dep does
    NOT introduce a new asymmetric-registration risk per CLAUDE.md §10 F.1
    because the upload endpoint is itself part of the same compound gate
    surface (both NullTextExtractor + NullRagService cover the
    compound-OFF branch).

    Update or add unit tests covering:
    - On successful upload, IndexSessionFileAsync is called exactly once with
      the expected (tenantId, sessionId, documentId, fileName) arguments
    - On successful upload, ChatSessionManager.UpdateSessionCacheAsync is
      called with a session whose UploadedFiles has exactly one new entry
      (or N+1 if already had files)
    - On 21st upload to a session that already has 20 files, returns 400
      ProblemDetails with errorCode `"summarize.too-many-files"` and the
      session is NOT mutated (cap-check happens BEFORE indexing)
    - Pre-existing Redis writes still happen unchanged (back-compat for any
      consumer that still reads from doc-upload:/doc-binary:/doc-upload-meta:
      keys directly)

    Acceptance: after this task ships AND deploys to Dev, the SessionSummarizeOrchestrator
    invoked with the session ID can find files via `session.UploadedFiles` and
    can retrieve content from spaarke-session-files AI Search index. Per-task
    publish-size verification per R5 CLAUDE.md §10: report compressed BFF size
    + delta vs baseline.
  </prompt>

