  <constraints>
    <constraint>R5 reuse mandate (spec §2.11): use existing IRagIndexingPipeline.IndexSessionFileAsync and ChatSessionManager.UpdateSessionCacheAsync; do NOT create parallel implementations.</constraint>
    <constraint>ADR-010 DI minimalism: do NOT add new top-level Program.cs registrations; the deps (IRagIndexingPipeline, ChatSessionManager) already exist.</constraint>
    <constraint>ADR-014 tenant isolation: IndexSessionFileAsync call MUST pass tenantId AND sessionId so the spaarke-session-files index entries carry both partition keys.</constraint>
    <constraint>NFR-02 cap: defense-in-depth at endpoint boundary; reject 21st upload with 400 ProblemDetails (errorCode `summarize.too-many-files`) BEFORE calling IndexSessionFileAsync or mutating session.</constraint>
    <constraint>ADR-018 / R5 §3.2: no new feature flag introduced; behavior inherits the existing compound AI gate (Analysis:Enabled + DocumentIntelligence:Enabled).</constraint>
    <constraint>ADR-019 ProblemDetails: errorCode strings are CONTRACT — `summarize.too-many-files` must match SummarizeSessionEndpoint's existing constant.</constraint>
    <constraint>ADR-015: do NOT log extracted text content or original binary — metadata only.</constraint>
    <constraint>D-06 (ChatSessionManager): persistence happens via UpdateSessionCacheAsync (Redis + fire-and-forget Cosmos); do NOT bypass this seam.</constraint>
    <constraint>Per-task publish-size verification per CLAUDE.md §10: report compressed BFF size + delta in task notes.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step>Load notes/summarize-vertical-remediation-plan.md fully; confirm scope matches §3.1 and §4 row 032.</step>
    <step>Read ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs lines 124-407 + ChatSessionManager.cs lines 260-316 + RagIndexingPipeline.IndexSessionFileAsync signature; map exact insertion point and DI surface needed.</step>
    <step>Read existing unit tests in tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/ChatDocumentEndpointsTests.cs (if any) and tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManagerTests.cs for patterns.</step>
    <step>Implement the wiring per §3.1 of the remediation plan. Inject IRagIndexingPipeline; add cap check; build ChatSessionFile; persist via UpdateSessionCacheAsync.</step>
    <step>Add 4 unit tests per task acceptance criteria.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet build -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~ChatDocumentEndpoints"` — verify all pass.</step>
    <step>Run full unit suite — verify no regressions.</step>
    <step>Per CLAUDE.md §10: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed size; report delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline.</step>
    <step>Commit with conventional message; reference remediation plan.</step>
    <step>Update TASK-INDEX.md status 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>ChatDocumentEndpoints.UploadDocumentAsync injects IRagIndexingPipeline and calls IndexSessionFileAsync after Redis writes.</criterion>
    <criterion>On 200 response, ChatSession.UploadedFiles[] contains a new ChatSessionFile entry with the uploaded file's metadata + non-empty SearchDocumentIdsCsv.</criterion>
    <criterion>ChatSessionManager.UpdateSessionCacheAsync invoked once per successful upload; Redis hot path + fire-and-forget Cosmos write-through both execute (verified by mocks).</criterion>
    <criterion>21st upload returns 400 with errorCode `summarize.too-many-files` and session manifest unchanged.</criterion>
    <criterion>Pre-existing Redis writes (doc-upload:, doc-binary:, doc-upload-meta:) still happen on successful upload (back-compat).</criterion>
    <criterion>All existing ChatDocumentEndpoints tests still pass; new tests pass.</criterion>
    <criterion>Full unit suite (6223+ tests) passes; 0 regressions.</criterion>
    <criterion>BFF publish size reported; delta vs baseline ≤ +1 MB.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

